criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  non-progressive SCI with complete motor paralysis below T1; American Spinal Injury
             Association Impairment Scale (AIS) A or B

          -  18 - 60 years of age;

          -  longer than 2 years post injury;

          -  stable medical condition

          -  unable to voluntarily move all single joints of the legs;

          -  spinal cort lesion between C7 and Th10

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  ventilator dependent;

          -  painful musculoskeletal dysfunction, unhealed fracture, contracture, or pressure sore
             that might interfere with training;

          -  clinically significant depression or ongoing drug abuse;

          -  cardiovascular, respiratory, bladder, or renal disease unrelated to SCI;

          -  severe anemia (Hgb<8 g/dl) or hypovolemia; and HIV or AIDS related illness.
